data.title: Sterett et al v. TBM Carriers, Inc. et al
authors: US District Court for the Western District of Kentucky
data.meta_description: Motor Vehicle case filed on August 10, 2021  in the Kentucky Western District Court
data.text: September 24, 2021 Filing 10 ORDER: The Court grants Sterret Companies, LLC's extension to file an answer to November 5, 2021 based on the agreement of all the parties. This Notice of Electronic Filing is the Official ORDER for this entry. No document is attached. cc: Counsel (JM) September 23, 2021 Filing 9 Proposed Agreed Order by Sterett Companies, LLC. (Fauth, Lisa) Modified on 9/23/2021 to change event/docket text to "proposed agreed order." (JM). August 18, 2021 Filing 8 Summons Issued as to Third-Party Defendants PGP Exotic Auto Sales, Inc., Sterett Companies, LLC and William L Sterett, III. Counsel for Plaintiff is responsible for printing and serving the attached issued summons(es). (Attachments: #1 Summons issued to Third-Party Defendant Sterett Companies, #2 Summons issued to Third-Party Defendant William L. Sterett III) (JM) August 17, 2021 Filing 7 ANSWER to Complaint with Jury Demand , THIRD PARTY COMPLAINT against Sterett Companies, LLC, PGP Exotic Auto Sales, Inc., William L Sterett, III, John Doe Defendants 1-3, John Doe Companies 4-6 by Jose Alberto T. Goxcon, TBM Carriers, Inc., Roberto Ignacio M. Enriquez. (Attachments: #1 Summons PGP Exotic Auto Sales, Inc. Summons on Third-Party Complaint, #2 Summons Sterett Companies Summons on Third-Party Complaint, #3 Summons William L. Sterett III Summons on Third-Party Complaint) (Janik, Steven) Modified on 8/18/2021 to add additional Third-Party Defendants (JM). August 12, 2021 Filing 6 ORDER REASSIGNING CASE. Pursuant to General Order No. 2020-27, the instant action is REASSIGNED to the docket of Judge Benjamin Beaton for final disposition. cc:counsel; CM-BB (EAS) August 11, 2021 Filing 5 CLERK'S NOTICE OF REMOVAL LETTER sent to Ohio Circuit Court re #1 Notice of Removal. (DJT) August 11, 2021 Filing 4 TEXT ORDER by Senior Judge Joseph H. McKinley, Jr. on 8/11/21: This action is hereby REFERRED to the Honorable H. BRENT BRENNENSTUHL, United States Magistrate Judge, for determination of non-dispositive matters pursuant to Title 28, U.S.C. 636(b)(1)(A). Said Magistrate is empowered to conduct any hearings necessary for their resolution. This Notice of Electronic Filing is the Official ORDER for this entry. No document is attached.cc:counsel (DJT) August 11, 2021 Filing 3 Case Assignment (Random Selection): Case Assigned to Senior Judge Joseph H. McKinley, Jr.. (DJT) August 10, 2021 Filing 2 Corporate Disclosure Statement by TBM Carriers, Inc.. (DJT)
